{
  "texts": [
    "Regularization terms are maximum entropy method (MEM), total variation (TV), total squared variation (TSV), the ℓ 1 norm (ℓ 1), and the weighted-ℓ 1 (ℓ W 1), and these are described in M 87 * 2017 IV.",
    "S/N (Rogers et al. 1995; Blackburn et al. 2020).",
    "The distribution of images in the resulting Top Sets on the real M 87 * data is a proxy for the uncertainties due to different imaging strategies and assumptions.",
    "For each method we also defined a \"fiducial\" image by converting the model ρ NX of each Top Set image to an effective blurring width, averaged this width across all synthetic data sets, and found the set of parameters that produced the minimum effective blurring width.",
    "A summary of the Top Set parameters for each method is shown in Table 2."
  ]
}